---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';

const title = '聯盟揭露';
const description =
  'How ChinaTripBox handles affiliate links, advertising relationships, editorial independence, and travel product recommendations.';
const lastUpdated = 'July 14, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout title={`${title} | ChinaTripBox`} description={description} locale="zh-TW">
  <Header locale="zh-TW" />
  <main class="container-page py-12">
    <article class="prose-content article-body">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900">聯盟揭露</h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <p class="mt-4">
        ChinaTripBox is an independent travel planning site. Some pages may include affiliate
        links, advertising placements, or partner references. If you click an affiliate link and
        make a purchase, we may earn a commission at no extra cost to you.
      </p>

      <h2>What This Means For Readers</h2>
      <p>
        Affiliate income helps keep our guides and tools free. It does not change the price you pay
        and it does not give a partner control over our editorial advice.
      </p>

      <h2>Editorial Independence</h2>
      <p>
        Our recommendations should be useful before they are commercial. We prioritize practical
        traveler needs: whether a payment method works, whether an eSIM is easy to activate,
        whether a booking flow supports foreign passports, and what backup plan a visitor should
        prepare.
      </p>

      <h2>What We May Earn From</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>eSIM, mobile data, or connectivity partners.</li>
        <li>Travel booking, train, transfer, or ticketing partners.</li>
        <li>Advertising displayed on the site.</li>
        <li>Future paid travel-help or planning products, if clearly offered.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What We Do Not Do</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell official visas, immigration approvals, government services, banking
        services, or emergency support. We do not guarantee that a third-party product will work for
        every traveler, device, passport, bank, or itinerary.
      </p>

      <h2>How To Read Our Product Mentions</h2>
      <p>
        Treat product and service mentions as practical starting points, not guarantees. Always
        check the provider's current terms, coverage, refund policy, device compatibility, payment
        limits, and traveler eligibility before buying.
      </p>

      <h2>Questions</h2>
      <p>
        For questions about affiliate links, advertising, or a correction to a recommendation,
        please use our <a href="/zh-tw/contact/">contact page</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
